.TH HYPRPAPER 1 "2025-12-03" "hyprpaper 0.8.3" "Hyprland Ecosystem"
.SH NAME
hyprpaper \- fast Wayland wallpaper utility with IPC controls
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hyprpaper
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hyprpaper
is a fast wallpaper utility for Hyprland with the ability to dynamically
change wallpapers through IPC.
It supports per\-output wallpapers, multiple fit modes, preloading for
instant wallpaper changes, and fractional scaling.
.PP
Supported image formats include JPEG, PNG, BMP, WebP, and SVG.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIpath\fR
Set a custom configuration file path.
.TP
.BR \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is searched for at
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/hypr/hyprpaper.conf
or
.IR ~/.config/hypr/hyprpaper.conf .
A configuration file is not required.
.SS General options
.TP
.B ipc
Enable IPC functionality. Default: 1.
.TP
.B splash
Controls splash screen display. Default: 1.
.TP
.B splash_offset
Splash screen offset. Default: 20.
.TP
.B splash_opacity
Splash screen opacity. Default: 0.8.
.SS Wallpaper section
Wallpaper entries are defined as special categories:
.TP
.B monitor
Target monitor name.
.TP
.B path
Path to the image file or directory.
.TP
.B fit_mode
How the wallpaper fits the screen.
Valid values:
.BR cover ,
.BR contain ,
.BR fit ,
.BR tile .
Default: cover.
.TP
.B timeout
Timeout for automatic wallpaper changes (in seconds). Default: 0 (disabled).
.SH IPC
.B hyprpaper
exposes a Hyprwire IPC socket at
.IR $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/hypr/$HYPRLAND_INSTANCE_SIGNATURE/.hyprpaper.sock .
This allows runtime wallpaper changes without restarting the daemon.
.SH SYSTEMD INTEGRATION
.B hyprpaper
ships with a systemd user service:
.PP
.RS
.B systemctl \-\-user enable \-\-now hyprpaper.service
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR Hyprland (1),
.BR hyprctl (1)
.SH AUTHOR
The Hyprland Development Team
.SH BUGS
